<subSubSection id="EE3B77557CA7B8C2D909C0ED66EED22D" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" type="notes">
<paragraph id="DD867CDD806B63CD4110020083320895" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8283A4782EB7821F780907E7A8DBDE1F" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">
A common species on alkaline habitats (
<bibRefCitation id="6C542C895CE6C0877423B32EF602D400" author="Hils, MH" editor="Flora of North America Editorial Committee, eds." journalOrPublisher="New York and Oxford" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="Flora of North America North of Mexico" year="1993">Hils et al. 1993</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="A840994479FD3B8B8B66DB779859A169" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sarcobataceae" genus="Sarcobatus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sarcobatus vermiculatus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vermiculatus">Sarcobatus vermiculatus</taxonomicName>
was found in greatest abundance along the banks of a seasonally wet stream crossing due northeast of MDRS (Fig. 46). Previously placed within the 
<taxonomicName id="32BE6EC600CAFD85B7FA9F4E9CFFFA24" family="Chenopodiaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" rank="family">Chenopodiaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FFBDBF4D1538220B095273DA71AF84DC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sarcobataceae" genus="Sarcobatus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sarcobatus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Sarcobatus</taxonomicName>
is now recognized as the sole genus within the 
<taxonomicName id="322807E84C75172EF450AEAD2518FB51" family="Sarcobataceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" rank="family">Sarcobataceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4C820DCEBF8A6D990B787540CC8B253F" author="Behnke, H-D" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="495 - 507" title="Sarcobataceae - a new family of Caryophyllales" volume="46" year="1997">Behnke 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="880FE6E85D31FEFA94D0D9FEF5A976A2" author="APG III," journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="105 - 121" title="An update of the Angiosperm Phylogeny Group classification for the orders and families of flowering plants: APG III" volume="161" year="2009">APG III 2009</bibRefCitation>
). This species was previously recorded for the nearby San Rafael Swell (
<bibRefCitation id="154AB8A6A4DE0C41BF4A5384C2630E9F" author="Harris, JG" journalOrPublisher="Great Basin Naturalist" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="79 - 87" title="A vascular flora of the San Rafael Swell, Utah" volume="43" year="1983">Harris 1983</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
